extensions.description:
Punk Pavel Durov got arrested. Why? Because he built a P2P social media app where people could exchange words without the worry of surveillance. 

He gave the power back to the people, creating an encrypted communication channel for them. 

The usage of such tools could be subjective, but it’s mainly for the greater good of user privacy, which is more important than anything else in this world. 

Arresting him in the name of providing a platform to bad actors is a stupid argument. It's akin to arresting Vitalik for building Ethereum because any scammer can launch a memecoin on it and scam people. 

Such stupid arguments completely dodge the major benefits, so people always get the bad side. We should not keep quiet now—start the protest, make a daily trend of #FREEDUROV, and raise funds for him like we all did for Assange in the past. 

It’s a fight between crypto and evil governments, and you need to choose the crypto side as it promises a long-term better future.
